%2C%20and%20the%20superstars%20can%20land%20contracts%20that%20are%20many%20multiples%20larger%2C%20with%20bidding%20wars%20engorging%20deal%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20late%20January%2C%20it%20was%20Marshall%20Wace%20long-short%20equities%20PM%20Kevin%20Liu%20securing%20a%20%2450%20million%20bag%20to%20join%20Point72%2C%20Bloomberg%20reported.%20Peter%20Goodwin%20started%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpeter-goodwin-equities-fund-launch-longaeva-balyasny-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eown%20equities%20unit%20at%20Balyasny%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20September%2C%20and%20his%20haul%20was%20said%20to%20be%20closer%20to%20%2480%20million.%20Other%20examples%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-06-01%2Ftop-traders-see-120-million-paydays-as-hedge-funds-fight-for-talent%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enow%20abound%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20the%20image%20conjured%20in%20your%20mind%20is%20people%20laying%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40breakingbad%2Fvideo%2F7352227795478662433%3Flang%3Den%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egiant%20stack%20of%20bills%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20storage%20unit%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-money-walter-white-made-on-breaking-bad-2013-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C3%A0%20la%20%26quot%3BBreaking%20Bad%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20reality%20is%20often%20quite%20different.%20The%20mechanics%20of%20an%20eight-figure%20PM%20deal%20are%20more%20complex%20than%20the%20headline%20figures%20may%20suggest%2C%20and%20a%20PM%20could%20pocket%20many%20millions%20less%20%E2%80%94%20or%20significantly%20more%20%E2%80%94%20depending%20on%20how%20the%20deal%20is%20structured.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENecessity%20is%20the%20mother%20of%20invention%2C%20and%20amid%20the%20competition%20for%20top%20PMs%2C%20funds%20have%20come%20up%20with%20more%20creative%20and%20nuanced%20deal%20structures%20to%20lure%20employees%20%E2%80%94%20richer%20performance%20incentives%20for%20limited%20periods%2C%20relocation%20to%20tax-friendly%20countries%2C%20ownership%20of%20intellectual%20property%2C%20or%20money%20to%20hire%20a%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20compensation%20expenses%20soar%2C%20funds%20are%20also%20taking%20measures%20to%20protect%20themselves%20and%20their%20investors%20from%20the%20risks%20of%20a%20bad%20hire.%20Some%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhedge-funds-push-legal-limits-vet-trader-performance-claims-pnl-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eramped%20up%20efforts%20to%20vet%20PMs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20sometimes%20taking%20aggressive%20and%20legally%20murky%20measures%20to%20ensure%20the%20deals%20they're%20offering%20are%20justified%2C%20as%20Business%20Insider%20recently%20reported.%20Others%20are%20implementing%20compensation%20clawbacks%20and%20break-up%20fees%20into%20contracts%20to%20help%20keep%20a%20lid%20on%20rising%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20spoke%20with%20recruiters%2C%20hedge%20fund%20business%20development%20leaders%2C%20and%20PMs%20about%20the%20ins%20and%20outs%20of%20PM%20deals%20at%20multimanager%20hedge%20funds%2C%20as%20well%20as%20how%20they've%20evolved%20in%20recent%20years%20as%20head%20count%20has%20doubled%20and%20assets%20have%20grown%20by%20%24200%20billion.%20Many%20asked%20for%20anonymity%20to%20discuss%20a%20topic%20that's%20sensitive%20to%20clients%20or%20employers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20common%20components%20to%20any%20contract.%20Sign-on%20bonuses%20are%20coveted%20and%20important%20for%20getting%20some%20deals%20done%2C%20but%20they're%20only%20one%20aspect%20of%20the%20mosaic%20and%20typically%20a%20small%20portion%20of%20the%20overall%20deal%20value.%20The%20profit%20percentage%2C%20the%20primary%20form%20of%20compensation%20at%20these%20funds%2C%20remains%20the%20most%20crucial%20for%20many%20people%2C%20according%20to%20John%20Pierson%2C%20a%20longtime%20hedge-fund%20recruiter%20and%20the%20founder%20of%20search%20firm%20P2%20Investments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20these%20people%20are%20alphas.%20They%20believe%20in%20their%20IP%20and%20their%20performance%2C%26quot%3B%20Pierson%20added.%20%26quot%3BThey%20want%20that%20ongoing%20percentage.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20general%2C%20sources%20said%20large%20deals%20are%20more%20nuanced%20and%20the%20guarantees%20smaller%20than%20is%20often%20appreciated%2C%20and%20that%20while%20PM%20deals%20share%20common%20features%2C%20they're%20not%20one-size-fits-all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20become%20more%20%26quot%3Brare%20that%20one%20deal%20is%20the%20same%20as%20the%20other%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20headhunter%20said.%20%26quot%3BEverything%20is%20negotiable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2217c3a221-6c65-48e8-ab1f-2060c7ffdf0c%5C%22%3EWhat%20goes%20into%20an%208-figure%20hire%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20hedge-fund%20traders%20are%20often%20the%20hardest%20to%20extract.%20They're%20already%20highly%20compensated%20and%20typically%20in%20stable%20work%20situations.%20They%20usually%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwall-street-quant-battle-to-lock-up-traders-with-noncompetes-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elengthy%20noncompete%20agreements%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20sometimes%20requiring%20them%20to%20sit%20out%2012%20months%20or%20more.%20Dislodging%20them%20and%20smoothing%20away%20those%20frictions%20can%20take%20patience%2C%20creativity%2C%20and%2C%20yes%2C%20large%20piles%20of%20cash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20deals%20are%20increasingly%20tailored%20to%20the%20PM%20and%20contingent%20on%20a%20dizzying%20array%20of%20variables%2C%20there%20are%20common%20features%20to%20most%20contracts.%20Goldman%20Sachs%20highlighted%20several%20of%20these%20components%20in%20a%20recent%20report%20on%20multimanager%20hedge%20funds%2C%20based%20on%20interviews%20with%20hedge%20fund%20business%20development%20professionals%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3Ea%20percentage%20cut%20of%20the%20trading%20profits%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3Eupfront%20guarantees%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3Ebuyout%20of%20deferred%20compensation%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3Eaccelerator%20incentives%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20PMs%20earn%20a%20%3Cstrong%3Ebase%20salary%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20that's%20often%20around%20%24200%2C000%2C%20sources%20told%20BI.%20While%20very%20good%20money%20to%20most%20Americans%2C%20that's%20not%20worth%20getting%20out%20of%20bed%20for%20most%20of%20these%20professionals%20%E2%80%94%20a%20sum%20that%20won't%20cover%20their%20cost%20of%20living.%20Moreover%2C%20it%20is%20often%20treated%20as%20a%20draw%20or%20an%20advance%20on%20the%20future%20profits%20a%20PM%20will%20earn%2C%20according%20to%20recruiters%20and%20fund%20regulatory%20filings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Cstrong%3Eprofit%20payout%20percentage%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20is%20the%20primary%20lever%20at%20these%20eat-what-you-kill%20hedge%20funds.%20At%20top%20firms%2C%20PMs%20commonly%20receive%20at%20least%2020%25%20of%20the%20profits%20from%20their%20trading%20strategy%2C%20according%20to%20Goldman.%20But%20your%20mileage%20will%20vary%20%E2%80%94%20unproven%20PMs%20may%20command%2012%25%20to%2017%25%2C%20and%20some%20superstars%20have%20gotten%2030%25%2C%20headhunters%20said.%20So%2C%20for%20example%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3EIf%20a%20long-short%20equities%20PM%20is%20on%20a%2020%25%20deal%20and%20makes%20%24100%20million%20trading%20tech%20stocks%20like%20Nvidia%20and%20Meta%2C%20they%20get%20%2420%20million.%20If%20a%20PM%20makes%20%241%20billion%20betting%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennium-hedge-funds-glen-scheinberg-index-rebalance-tesla-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erebalancing%20of%20the%20Nasdaq%20or%20Russell%20indices%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20well%2C%20you%20can%20do%20the%20math.%20A%20portion%20is%20paid%20in%20cash%20and%20a%20portion%20is%20deferred%20and%20vests%20over%20time%2C%20the%20length%20varying%20by%20firm.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20there's%20%3Cstrong%3Ethe%20upfront%20guaranteed%20bonus%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eor%20sign-on%20bonus%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20aspect%20that%20people%20ogle%20and%20drool%20over.%20Switching%20employers%20comes%20with%20an%20opportunity%20cost.%20A%20PM%20will%20have%20to%20sit%20out%20their%20noncompete%2C%20and%20then%20they%20have%20to%20build%20out%20their%20trading%20operation%20on%20a%20new%20platform%20%E2%80%94%20time%20they%20could've%20spent%20earning%20more%20money%20at%20their%20existing%20employer.%20The%20fund%20may%20provide%20a%20sign-on%20bonus%20to%20compensate%20for%20that%20lost%20earning%20potential%2C%20though%20how%20much%20and%20with%20what%20strings%20attached%20varies%20significantly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20is%20really%20the%20lure%20to%20get%20people%20out%20of%20their%20firms%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20headhunter%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20buyout%20or%20%26quot%3Bmake-whole%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eis%20related%20and%20factors%20into%20the%20overall%20guaranteed%20amount.%20Traders%20are%20often%20paid%20a%20portion%20of%20their%20annual%20comp%20in%20cash%20and%20a%20portion%20in%20deferred%20compensation%20that%20vests%20over%20time%2C%20and%20an%20early%20departure%20means%20sacrificing%20unvested%20comp%20from%20their%20prior%20shop.%20Additionally%2C%20they%20may%20have%20generated%20trading%20profits%20that%20won't%20be%20paid%20out%20if%20they%20leave%20mid-year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3EA%20talented%20PM%20may%20receive%20a%20%2420%20million%20upfront%20sign-on%20bonus%2C%20in%20part%20to%20compensate%20for%20their%20lost%20deferred%20comp%2C%20in%20part%20for%20their%20time%20sitting%20idle%2C%20and%20in%20part%20because%20they're%20in%20high%20demand.%20Deals%20covering%20more%20than%20two%20years%20are%20rare%20but%20not%20unprecedented%2C%20recruiters%20and%20BD%20professionals%20said%2C%20and%20these%20%26quot%3Bguarantees%26quot%3B%20increasingly%20come%20with%20catches%20and%20caveats%20(more%20on%20that%20below).%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20%26quot%3Baccelerator%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20is%20connected%20to%20the%20profit%20cut%2C%20essentially%20supercharging%20that%20payout%20for%20a%20determined%20amount%20of%20time%20or%20up%20to%20a%20fixed%20amount%20of%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3EInstead%20of%20just%20forking%20over%20more%20hard%20cash%20to%20entice%20a%20PM%2C%20the%20fund%20may%20offer%20to%20increase%20the%20percentage%20payout%20from%2020%25%20to%2030%25%20on%20the%20first%20%2420%20million%20in%20profits%2C%20as%20an%20example.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThen%20everyone's%20got%20skin%20in%20the%20game%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20headhunter%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccelerators%20can%20also%20be%20structured%20as%20a%20performance%20trigger%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3EThe%20payout%20level%20increases%20if%20a%20threshold%20or%20milestone%20is%20reached.%20For%20example%2C%20trading%20profits%20eclipse%20%24100%20million%20or%20the%20Sharpe%20ratio%20%E2%80%94%20the%20return%20relative%20to%20the%20risk%20taken%20%E2%80%94%20exceeds%201.5.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20accelerator%20%26quot%3Bhas%20seen%20the%20greatest%20increase%20in%20prevalence%20over%20the%20last%20one%20to%20two%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Goldman's%20interviews%20with%20BD%20teams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvery%20firm%20wants%20to%20do%20accelerators%20before%20giving%20over%20hard%20cash%2C%26quot%3B%20another%20headhunter%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20previously%20mentioned%2C%20some%20strategies%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20systematic%20trades%20heavily%20dependent%20on%20market%20data%20and%20technology%20%E2%80%94%20can%20take%20longer%20than%20others%20to%20set%20up%20and%20become%20profitable%2C%20making%20this%20provision%20%26quot%3Bhollow%26quot%3B%20if%20the%20time%20period%20is%20too%20short%2C%20according%20to%20one%20recruiter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20they%20have%20their%20IP%20that%20helps%20a%20lot%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221262%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22huell%20money%20breaking%20bad%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F52124584ecad041839000018%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22711%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EAMC%20screencap%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22314b1859-2e5e-40ce-a932-850e92235044%5C%22%3EMoney%20talks%2C%20but%20creativity%20helps%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIntellectual%20property%20ownership%2C%20especially%20for%20quantitative%20strategies%2C%20is%20one%20of%20the%20myriad%20factors%20that%20also%20play%20into%20a%20hire%20and%20can%20significantly%20affect%20the%20total%20value%2C%20especially%20as%20%26quot%3Bbespoke%20structures%20for%20each%20PM%20are%20increasingly%20normal%2C%26quot%3B%20Goldman%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMillennium%2C%20the%20largest%20multimanager%20by%20assets%20and%20head%20count%2C%20is%20known%20for%20its%20creativity%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbusiness-development-execs-to-know-at-top-hedge-funds-2024-4%23millennium%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egetting%20deals%20over%20the%20line%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Yes%2C%20it%20can%20back%20up%20a%20Brinks%20truck%20to%20hire%20a%20PM%2C%20but%20it%20is%20also%20known%20to%20allow%20PMs%20to%20leave%20with%20the%20IP%20they've%20built%20at%20the%20hedge%20fund%20%E2%80%94%20though%20Millennium%20retains%20a%20license%20as%20well%20and%20can%20continue%20to%20make%20money%20off%20of%20it%2C%20according%20to%20three%20recruiters%20familiar%20with%20the%20firm.%20It's%20not%20a%20bargaining%20chip%20offered%20by%20every%20firm%20or%20to%20every%20PM%2C%20but%20it's%20an%20important%20consideration%20to%20some%20traders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMillennium%20has%20also%20opened%20new%20locations%20to%20help%20win%20over%20candidates%2C%20as%20it%20did%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhedge-funds-talent-middle-east-capital-dubai-abu-dhabi-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPratik%20Madhvani%20in%20Dubai%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20industry%20insiders%20previously%20told%20BI.%20Relocation%20to%20a%20more%20tax-friendly%20location%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhedge-fund-rich-taxes-labour-london-uk-relocation-milan-dubai-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMilan%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Zurich%2C%20or%20Puerto%20Rico%2C%20for%20instance%20%E2%80%94%20has%20generally%20become%20a%20more%20popular%20inducement%2C%20three%20headhunters%20said.%20(Millennium%20declined%20to%20comment%20for%20this%20story).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECost-sharing%20is%20also%20a%20key%20consideration.%20Investment%20teams%20incur%20a%20variety%20of%20expenses%2C%20such%20as%20market%20data%2C%20hardware%2C%20software%2C%20legal%20fees%2C%20and%20connections%20to%20trading%20venues%20and%20brokers.%20Some%20strategies%20are%20pricier%20to%20run%20than%20others%2C%20and%20these%20costs%20can%20erode%20the%20PM's%20annual%20profit%20cut%2C%20depending%20on%20how%20they're%20split.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuilding%20out%20a%20team%20is%20also%20expensive.%20For%20the%20right%20PM%2C%20the%20fund%20may%20cover%20the%20guarantees%20and%20recruiting%20fees%20to%20hire%20a%20staff%2C%20which%20amounts%20to%20millions.%20Goodwin's%20deal%20at%20Balyasny%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20included%20money%20to%20hire%20a%20team%2C%20according%20to%20a%20person%20familiar%20with%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fdb05070-f3d2-4f69-89ab-9f99816ee588%5C%22%3EWhat's%20the%20deal%3F%3C%2Fh4%3E%3Cp%3EA%20non-exhaustive%20list%20of%20factors%20affecting%20a%20PM's%20contract%20value%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EProfit%20percentage%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGuaranteed%20bonuses%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBuyout%20of%20deferred%20comp%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAccelerators%20and%20performance%20triggers%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERelocation%20to%20a%20tax-friendly%20locale%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMoney%20to%20hire%20a%20team%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIP%20ownership%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECost-sharing%2C%20such%20as%20who%20pays%20for%20market%20data%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EClawbacks%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBreakup%20fees%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20key%20parameters%20in%20negotiations%20include%20risk%20limits%20and%20the%20amount%20of%20capital%20a%20PM%20has%20access%20to%20trade%20with%20%E2%80%94%20key%20factors%20affecting%20how%20much%20money%20they%20can%20generate.%20While%20a%20fund%20offering%20a%20generous%2030%25%20payout%20may%20seem%20like%20a%20no-brainer%2C%20it's%20usually%20less%20attractive%20than%20a%20firm%20offering%2020%25%20but%20with%20world-class%20risk%20and%20trading%20technology%20and%20twice%20as%20much%20money%20to%20trade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPierson%20said%20the%20smaller%20or%20second-tier%20funds%20can't%20offer%20the%20gaudy%20guaranteed%20cash%20a%20top-tier%20fund%20can%2C%20but%20they%20can%20compete%20by%20offering%20a%20higher%20percentage%20payout%20and%20a%20longer%20leash%20for%20drawdowns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20they%20can%20do%20to%20compete%20is%20guarantee%20a%20longer%20runway%2C%26quot%3B%20Pierson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2229de3acb-202c-4c49-a820-3fc3ecd37c66%5C%22%3ECatches%20and%20caveats%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20factor%20complicating%20compensation%20packages%20is%20the%20caveats%20funds%20now%20add%20to%20contracts.%20When%20people%20see%20an%208-figure%20PM%20deal%2C%20what%20some%20don't%20realize%20is%20that%20often%20just%20a%20portion%20of%20the%20reported%20figure%20is%20fully%20guaranteed%2C%20several%20industry%20sources%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20many%20contracts%2C%20part%20of%20the%20upfront%20sign-on%20bonus%20is%20a%20draw%2C%20meaning%20the%20payment%20is%20earned%20back%20through%20future%20performance.%20They%20may%20also%20be%20subject%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2024-12-06%2Fexoduspoint-to-claw-back-bonuses-from-more-employees-who-quit%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclawback%20provisions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20requiring%20employees%20to%20repay%20a%20portion%20of%20their%20comp%20if%20they%20leave%20or%20are%20fired%20before%20a%20certain%20period%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20contract%20template%20seen%20by%20BI%20describes%20an%20accelerator%20provision%20%E2%80%94%20increasing%20the%20percentage%20payout%20from%2020%25%20to%2030%25%20%E2%80%94%20until%20a%20certain%20threshold.%20But%20it%20also%20notes%20that%20this%20additional%20comp%20must%20be%20repaid%20within%2030%20days%20if%20the%20employee%20leaves%20or%20is%20fired%20within%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20clawbacks%20have%20become%20a%20big%20part%20of%20these%20big%20deals%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20of%20the%20recruiters.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20becoming%20more%20prevalent%20as%20a%20way%20for%20clients%20to%20keep%20people%20out%20of%20the%20market%20to%20some%20extent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBreakup%20fees%20are%20more%20commonly%20associated%20with%20multibillion-dollar%20mergers%20and%20acquisitions%2C%20but%20they%20now%20apply%20to%20portfolio%20manager%20hires%20as%20well.%20Recruiting%20is%20costly%20and%20time-consuming%2C%20and%20because%20of%20noncompete%20clauses%2C%20it%20can%20be%20months%20or%20even%20years%20from%20when%20a%20PM%20signs%20a%20contract%20to%20when%20they%20actually%20join.%20Some%20PMs%20get%20sweeter%20offers%20during%20their%20sit-out%20and%20renege%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcitadel-rates-pm-george-arzeno-hired-point72-balyasny-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eopting%20to%20join%20a%20different%20firm%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20to%20return%20to%20their%20old%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOve