ption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3BAlyssa%20Powell%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESaving%20for%20retirement%20might%20not%20seem%20urgent%20in%20your%2020s%2C%20but%20it's%20the%20perfect%20time%20to%20start.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt's%20important%20to%20build%20healthy%20financial%20habits%20like%20saving%20regularly%20and%20paying%20off%20debt.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHere%20are%205%20smart%20money%20moves%20to%20get%20a%20head%20start%20on%20your%20retirement.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20popular%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fhow-much-do-i-need-to-retire%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretirement%20rule%20of%20thumb%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20to%20have%20saved%20around%2010%20times%20your%20salary%20at%20the%20time%20you%20decide%20to%20stop%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20number%20can%20seem%20daunting%20for%20twenty-somethings%20who%20recently%20entered%20the%20workforce%20and%20are%20in%20the%20process%20of%20figuring%20out%20their%20personal%20finances.%20But%20with%20the%20right%20plan%2C%20your%2020s%20provide%20a%20golden%20opportunity%20to%20set%20yourself%20up%20for%20a%20successful%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20some%20key%20considerations%20for%20twenty-somethings%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20retirement%20planning%2C%20according%20to%20BNY%20Wealth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20everyday%20living%20expenses%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20food%2C%20entertainment%2C%20and%20transportation%20%E2%80%94%20will%20stay%20largely%20consistent.%20However%2C%20expect%20your%20housing%20and%20healthcare%20expenses%20to%20shift%20in%20retirement%2C%20according%20to%20Fidelity.%20Typically%2C%20retirees%20spend%20less%20on%20housing%20costs%20as%20they%20move%2C%20downsize%2C%20or%20pay%20off%20their%20mortgage.%20But%20healthcare%20costs%20tend%20to%20increase%20with%20age%20and%20can%20be%20wildly%20unpredictable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20this%20in%20mind%2C%20the%20first%20step%20to%20establishing%20a%20retirement%20plan%20is%20to%20build%20healthy%20financial%20habits%20in%20your%2020s.%20BNY%20Wealth%20recommends%20aiming%20to%20%3Cstrong%3Esave%20at%20least%2010-15%25%20of%20every%20paycheck%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20Ashley%20Weeks%2C%20wealth%20strategist%20at%20TD%20Wealth%2C%20recommends%20more%20if%20possible%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20tell%20clients%20and%20their%20kids%2015%25%20of%20your%20pre-tax%20income%2C%26quot%3B%20Weeks%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAutomating%20your%20savings%20can%20help%20people%20achieve%20this%20goal%20by%20creating%20a%20consistent%20savings%20habit%20early%20on%2C%20according%20to%20Fidelity.%20You%20can%20set%20up%20a%20direct%20deposit%20split%20to%20automatically%20send%20a%20portion%20of%20your%20paycheck%20into%20a%20savings%20account%20or%20a%20recurring%20savings%20transfer%20through%20your%20bank%20to%20schedule%20automatic%20transfers%20on%20a%20custom%20schedule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20your%20savings%20should%20go%20to%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fwhat-is-an-emergency-fund%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Eemergency%20fund%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20can%20fund%20three%20to%20six%20months%20of%20living%20expenses.%20This%20creates%20a%20financial%20cushion%20if%20an%20unexpected%20life%20change%20occurs%2C%20such%20as%20losing%20your%20job.%20In%20the%20case%20that%20extraneous%20costs%20pop%20up%2C%20an%20emergency%20fund%20allows%20you%20to%20weather%20the%20storm%20without%20accumulating%20credit%20card%20debt%20or%20taking%20out%20loans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20you%20build%20up%20your%20emergency%20fund%2C%20also%20make%20sure%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20your%20%3Cstrong%3Eemployer's%20retirement%20plan%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20such%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-401k%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E401(k)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-403b%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E403(b)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fsep-ira%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESEP%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E.%20You%20should%20adjust%20your%20contributions%20as%20you%20progress%20in%20your%20career%2C%20according%20to%20both%20BNY%20Wealth%20and%20Weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPay%20yourself%20first%2C%26quot%3B%20Weeks%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnytime%20you%20get%20a%20pay%20increase%2C%20it's%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20add%20to%20your%20contributions%20to%20a%20workplace%20plan%20or%20an%20IRA%20if%20there's%20room%20in%20the%20budget.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESaving%20up%20to%2015%25%20of%20each%20paycheck%20and%20putting%20away%20money%20for%20retirement%20can%20be%20a%20tall%20order%20for%20many%2C%20especially%20recent%20college%20graduates%20just%20starting%20their%20careers.%20Paying%20down%20student%20loans%20can%20complicate%20this%20goal%20even%20further.%20However%2C%20twenty-somethings%20should%20know%20that%20there%20are%20still%20ways%20to%20save%20for%20retirement%2C%20even%20while%20paying%20down%20debt.%20Weeks%20points%20out%20that%20the%20SECURE%202.0%20Act%20allows%20employers%20to%20provide%20a%20%3Cstrong%3Estudent%20loan%20payment%20retirement%20match%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20If%20an%20employee%20makes%20payments%20toward%20their%20student%20loans%2C%20their%20employer%20can%20treat%20those%20payments%20as%20if%20they%20were%20retirement%20contributions%20and%20match%20them%20in%20the%20company's%20retirement%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20provision%20is%20optional%20for%20employers%2C%20so%20Weeks%20encourages%20employees%20to%20check%20their%20specific%20company%20policy.%20If%20your%20employer%20offers%20a%20student%20loan%20payment%20retirement%20match%2C%20you%20don't%20need%20to%20miss%20out%20on%20retirement%20contributions%20to%20pay%20down%20loans.%20Once%20loans%20are%20paid%20off%2C%20you%20should%20increase%20your%20retirement%20plan%20contributions%2C%20BNY%20Wealth%20recommends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwenty-somethings%20should%20also%20make%20sure%20they%20have%20%3Cstrong%3Esufficient%20insurance%20coverage%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20according%20to%20BNY%20Wealth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlthough%20the%2020s%20are%20often%20the%20healthiest%20years%2C%20we%20believe%20that%20it%20is%20important%20for%20people%20in%20this%20age%20bracket%20to%20get%20health%20insurance%20%E2%80%94%20not%20only%20because%20injury%20and%20illness%20can%20happen%20to%20anybody%2C%20but%20it%20can%20saddle%20one%20with%20tremendous%20debts%2C%26quot%3B%20BNY%20Wealth%20wrote%20in%20a%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20people%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Frenting-vs-buying-house-pros-cons%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erenting%20a%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frent-mortgage-affordability-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaffordable%20option%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20buying.%20If%20that's%20the%20case%20for%20you%2C%20BNY%20Wealth%20recommends%20getting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhomeowners-insurance%2Fbest-renters-insurance-companies%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erenters%20insurance%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20protect%20your%20personal%20property%20and%20valuable%20possessions.%20This%20will%20decrease%20the%20risk%20of%20unexpected%20expenses%20and%20loans%20that%20could%20derail%20your%20savings%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20twenty-somethings%2C%20time%20is%20on%20your%20side%20when%20saving%20for%20retirement%2C%20thanks%20to%20the%20power%20of%20compounding%20returns.%20With%20a%20long%20runway%2C%20your%20original%20investment%20has%20more%20time%20to%20generate%20returns%2C%20which%20are%20then%20reinvested%2C%20leading%20to