0a%20chance%20to%20stand%20out%20and%20using%20more%20individualized%20benefits%20to%20signal%20to%20workers%20that%20they%20%3Cem%3Edo%3C%2Fem%3E%20care%20%E2%80%94%20while%20hoping%20workers%20repay%20them%20with%20higher%20rates%20of%20productivity%20and%20loyalty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20aren't%20likely%20to%20pick%20a%20job%20for%20a%20one-off%20benefit.%20But%20companies%20are%20focusing%20on%20%26quot%3Bflexible%2C%20personalized%2C%20and%20inclusive%26quot%3B%20perks%20that%20appeal%20to%20employees%20across%20generations%2C%20Theresa%20Adams%2C%20a%20human-resources%20knowledge%20advisor%20with%20SHRM%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BEmployers%20are%20trying%20to%20make%20benefits%20more%20unique%20to%20their%20employees%20to%20gain%20top%20talent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20used%20to%20measure%20how%20successful%20their%20benefits%20were%20by%20how%20many%20workers%20used%20them%2C%20but%20the%20focus%20has%20shifted%2C%20said%20Samantha%20Saxby%2C%20the%20director%20of%20marketing%20for%20the%20National%20Human%20Resources%20Association%20and%20a%20managing%20director%20at%20the%20benefits%20company%20Perky.%20%26quot%3BInstead%20of%20prioritizing%20sheer%20numbers%2C%20they're%20investing%20in%20targeted%2C%20high-impact%20support%20that%20enhances%20employee%20well-being%20and%20commitment%2C%20even%20if%20it%20serves%20a%20smaller%20segment%20of%20the%20workforce%2C%26quot%3B%20Saxby%20said.%20She%20cited%20robust%20benefits%20for%20new%20parents%20as%20an%20example%20%E2%80%94%20they%20might%20be%20accessed%20by%20only%20a%20small%20number%20of%20employees%20at%20any%20given%20time%20but%20create%20more%20engagement%2C%20satisfaction%2C%20and%20retention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20software%20company%20Pipedrive%2C%20its%20750-some%20employees%20can%20receive%20five%20days%20of%20%26quot%3Bpawternity%20leave%26quot%3B%20when%20they%20adopt%20a%20pet%20(as%20long%20as%20it%20has%20furry%20paws%3B%20sorry%2C%20turtles).%20It%20also%20offers%20%26quot%3Bcompassionate%20leave%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20expanded%20bereavement%20category%20for%20anything%20from%20the%20death%20of%20a%20loved%20one%20or%20a%20pet%20to%20a%20breakup.%20The%20benefits%2C%20added%20late%20last%20year%2C%20signal%20that%20Pipedrive%20isn't%20catering%20only%20to%20traditional%20family%20structures.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20about%20recognition%20that%20everyone's%20situation%20is%20different%2C%26quot%3B%20Tanya%20Channing%2C%20Pipedrive's%20chief%20people%20and%20culture%20officer%2C%20said.%20The%20company's%20benefits%20are%20ways%20to%20showcase%20its%20culture%2C%20she%20said%2C%20and%20Pipedrive%20trusts%20its%20employees%20to%20work%20hard%20and%20not%20abuse%20them.%20If%20management%20strictly%20polices%20who%20takes%20what%20benefits%20when%20just%20a%20small%20number%20of%20people%20might%20exploit%20them%2C%20%26quot%3Byou're%20penalizing%20the%2098%25%20who%20don't%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAcross%20all%20industries%2C%20companies'%20health%20benefits%20have%20stayed%20relatively%20flat%2C%20with%20some%20falling%20slightly%2C%20a%20recent%20Society%20for%20Human%20Resource%20Management%20survey%20of%20more%20than%204%2C500%20employers%20found.%20In%20the%20survey%2C%20the%20proportion%20of%20companies%20offering%20paid%20mental%20health%20days%20dropped%20from%2020%25%20in%202022%20to%2016%25%20in%202024%2C%20and%20dependent-care%20flexible%20spending%20accounts%20fell%20by%206%25%2C%20with%2058%25%20of%20employers%20offering%20them%20in%202024.%20Surveyed%20companies%20offering%20access%20to%20elder%20care%20services%20and%20information%20fell%20from%2011%25%20in%202020%20to%207%25%20in%202024.%20And%20just%201%25%20gave%20employees%20subsidies%20for%20elder%20care%2C%20while%203%25%20handed%20out%20childcare%20subsidies.%20Dependent%20care%20is%20an%20increasingly%20valuable%20but%20still%20rare%20perk%20as%20Gen%20Xers%20and%20millennials%20find%20themselves%20caring%20for%20children%2C%20parents%2C%20or%2C%20sometimes%2C%20both%20at%20once.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%20companies%2C%20holding%20on%20to%20benefits%20is%20a%20way%20to%20signal%20their%20values.%20Run%20for%20Something%2C%20which%20recruits%20and%20supports%20young%20progressive%20political%20candidates%2C%20offers%20workers%20a%20four-day%20workweek%20and%20fully%20covered%20health%20insurance%20premiums%2C%20along%20with%20a%20%24500%20%26quot%3Btreat%20yourself%26quot%3B%20stipend%20to%20be%20spent%20on%20anything%20from%20a%20nice%20dinner%20to%20a%20night%20in%20a%20hotel%2C%20to%20encourage%20work-life%20balance.%20Amanda%20Litman%2C%20Run%20for%20Something's%20cofounder%2C%20sees%20the%20company's%20benefits%20as%20central%20to%20its%20mission.%20And%20as%20more%20places%20look%20to%20roll%20back%20diversity%2C%20equity%2C%20and%20inclusion%20initiatives%2C%20Run%20for%20Something%20has%20no%20plans%20to%20change%20its%20policies%20about%20being%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdei-programs-america-diversity-equity-inclusion-pushback-how-to-fix-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einclusive%20workplace%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20fundamental%20to%20the%20way%20that%20we%20operate%2C%26quot%3B%20Litman%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BEven%20if%20it%20wasn't%20a%20moral%20good%20%E2%80%94%20to%20hire%20the%20best%20possible%20people%20of%20all%20backgrounds%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20good%20for%20business.%26quot%3B%20It%20seems%20to%20be%20working%3A%20Litman%20said%20the%20team%20of%2030%20had%20seen%20incredibly%20low%20turnover%2C%20and%20each%20time%20the%20company%20lists%20a%20new%20position%2C%20hundreds%20of%20people%20apply.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20flashy%20benefit%20can%20catch%20the%20eyes%20of%20prospective%20workers.%20Grant%20Lowe%2C%20a%20technical%20writer%20at%20the%20streaming%20service%20Philo%2C%20was%20applying%20for%20his%20job%20two%20years%20ago%2C%20when%20one%20benefit%20stood%20out%3A%20a%20%242%2C000%20bonus%20that%20gets%20paid%20out%20when%20employees%20take%20their%20vacation.%20It%20was%20the%20%26quot%3Bcherry%20on%20top%26quot%3B%20of%20an%20already%20appealing%20role%2C%20he%20said.%20Last%20month%2C%20Lowe%20flew%20to%20Hawaii%20and%20visited%20his%20two%20brothers%2C%20the%20first%20time%20the%20three%20were%20together%20in%20eight%20years.%20%26quot%3BThe%20signal%20that%20it%20sends%20is%2C%20'Hey%2C%20we%20want%20you%20to%20take%20that%20time%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20is%20to%20get%20people%20to%20take%20%3Cem%3Eat%20least%3C%2Fem%3E%20two%20weeks%20of%20their%20unlimited%20PTO%2C%20said%20Pearlie%20Oni%2C%20Philo's%20head%20of%20people.%20The%20company%20also%20allows%20employees%20to%20work%20fully%20remote%20but%20will%20pay%20a%20%24500%20monthly%20bonus%20to%20employees%20who%20commit%20to%20being%20in%20the%20office%20three%20days%20a%20week%2C%20as%20well%20as%20subsidies%20to%20help%20with%20commuter%20costs.%20It's%20the%20kind%20of%20balance%20that%20lets%20people%20choose%20between%20extra%20cash%20or%20being%20home%20for%20kids%20after%20school.%20Forcing%20people%20back%20to%20their%20cubicles%20doesn't%20work%2C%20Oni%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20vibe%20is%20going%20to%20be%20off.%26quot%3B%20With%20the%20bonus%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20can%20get%20the%20people%20that%20want%20to%20be%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20grocery%20and%20restaurant%20costs%20rising%20sharply%20since%20the%20pandemic%2C%20money%20to%20splurge%20on%20food%20is%20another%20valuable%20benefit.%20Since%202020%20the%20cloud-based%20web%20accessibility%20company%20AudioEye%20has%20offered%20employees%20a%20%2420-a-family-member%20weekly%20meal%20credit.%20%26quot%3BThe%20shift%20to%20remote%20work%20blurred%20the%20lines%20between%20work%20and%20home%2C%20and%20we%20wanted%20to%20encourage%20our%20employees%20to%20step%20away%20from%20their%20screens%20and%20enjoy%20quality%20time%20with%20their%20families%2C%26quot%3B%20Brittani%20Morelli%2C%20the%20company's%20vice%20president%20of%20human%20resources%2C%20told%20me%20in%20an%20email.%20Close%20to%20two-thirds%20of%20employees%20use%20it%20regularly%2C%20she%20said%2C%20and%20the%20company%20also%20covers%20some%20in-office%20lunches%20as%20people%20return%20to%20working%20in%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegardless%20of%20what%20the%20benefits%20are%2C%20the%20days%20of%20dangling%20lavish%20perks%20in%20front%20of%20people%20in%20lieu%20of%20good%20salaries%20and%20health%20benefits%20are%20over.%20Mostly%2C%20people%20need%20to%20like%20the%20work%20they%20do%20and%20feel%20valued%20by%20compensation%20and%20benefits%20that%20actually%20support%20their%20lives.%20In%20the%202010s%2C%20%26quot%3Bthey%20all%20needed%20to%20have%20this%20long%20laundry%20list%20of%2C%20'Here's%20all%20the%20quirky%20things%20we%20offer%2C'%20just%20to%20seem%20like%20they%20did%20a%20lot%2C%26quot%3B%20Amy%20Spurling%2C%20the%20CEO%20and%20founder%20of%20the%20HR%20services%20company%20Compt%2C%20said.%20Now%2C%20that%20can%20backfire.%20%26quot%3BThe%20market%20and%20the%20employees%20are%20smarter%20than%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlexibility%20in%20benefits%20is%20the%20future%2C%20Spurling%20said.%20If%20you%20offer%20pet%20grooming%2C%20that's%20attractive%20to%20pet%20owners%20only.%20The%20same%20goes%20for%20fertility%20or%20commuter%20benefits%20for%20all%20%E2%80%94%20some%20will%20love%20the%20stipends%2C%20and%20those%20who%20don't%20need%20them%20may%20shrug%20them%20off.%20But%20personalized%20stipends%20for%20things%20like%20childcare%20or%20wellness%2C%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkers-say-employers-should-pay-for-commute-return-to-office-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecommuter%20benefits%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20lunch%20stipends%20for%20companies%20with%20RTO%20mandates%2C%20can%20help%20people%20to%20pay%20for%20what%20they%20need%20as%20they%20need%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20costs%20for%20workers%20pile%20up%2C%20fun%20perks%20won't%20be%20the%20whole%20answer.%20Ultimately%2C%20people%20want%20to%20work%20jobs%20they%20like%20for%20equitable%20pay%20and%20work-life%20balance.%20The%20real%20benefit%20comes%20when%20a%20company's%20perks%20can%20speak%20to%20and%20influence%20its%20culture%20overall.%20And%20the%20more%20that%20the%20line%20between%20work%20life%20and%20personal%20life%20blurs%2C%20bosses%20may%20have%20to%20keep%20doing%20more%20to%20show%20they%20care%20about%20your%20feelings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Famanda-hoover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAmanda%20Hoover%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%20covering%20the%20tech%20industry.%20She%20writes%20about%20the%20biggest%20tech%20companies%20and%20trends.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstartups-showering-employees-wild-perks-pet-leave-college-funds-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739351282000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ab9fb37bb3f854015c87ae%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstartups-showering-employees-wild-perks-pet-leave-college-funds-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20Big%20Tech%20cuts%20back%20on%20cushy%20perks%2C%20startups%20are%20offering%20everything%20from%20college%20funds%20for%20employees'%20kids%20to%20'compassionate%20leave'%20for%20breakups.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ahoover%40insider.com%20(Amanda%20Hoover)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstartups-showering-employees-wild-perks-pet-leave-college-funds-2025-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Elon%20Musk's%20xAI%20plans%20massive%20hiring%20spree%20of%20thousands%20to%20train%20Grok%2C%20employees%20say%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Men%20working%20on%20laptop%20on%20conveyor%20belt%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67aa5a77eb4be2fff9a42817%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%C2%A0%3Cp%3Einsta_photos%2FGetty%2C%20PhonlamaiPhoto%2FGetty%2C%20Ava%20Horton%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ExAI%20plans%20to%20add%20thousands%20of%20%26quot%3BAI%20tutors%26quot%3B%20this%20year%2C%20three%20employees%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20company%20currently%20employs%20over%20900%20tutors%20who%20typically%20work%20on%20training%20Grok%2C%20xAI's%20chatbot.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20hiring%20ramp%20up%20comes%20as%20Musk's%20company%20looks%20to%20gain%20an%20edge%20in%20the%20AI%20arms%20race.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ExAI%20plans%20to%20hire%20thousands%20of%20people%20this%20year%20to%20help%20train%20its%20chatbot%20Grok%2C%20three%20employees%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20as%20it%20looks%20to%20gain%20an%20edge%20in%20the%20AI%20arms%20race%20with%20OpenAI%2C%20Meta%2C%20and%20Google.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EElon%20Musk's%20artificial%20intelligence%20company%20has%20five%20job%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.ai%2Fcareers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elistings%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20data%20annotation%20roles%2C%20seeking%20bilingual%20workers%20and%20legal%20and%20STEM%20specialists.%20The%20employees%20said%20they%20were%20told%20by%20managers%20about%20the%20hiring%20ramp-up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ExAI%20employs%20more%20than%20900%20data%20annotators%2C%20which%20it%20calls%20%26quot%3BAI%20tutors%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20a%20tally%20of%20the%20company's%20internal%20Slack.%20It%20brought%20in%20hundreds%20of%20tutors%20in%20preparation%20for%20the%20November%20presidential%20election%2C%20according%20to%20six%20current%20and%20former%20employees.%20The%20workers%20asked%20to%20remain%20anonymous%20in%20order%20to%20avoid%20professional%20reprisal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20has%20repeatedly%20emphasized%20the%20potential%20of%20AI%2C%20and%20he%20has%20used%20his%20startup%20to%20wade%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fxai-openai-salary-workers-pay-data-comparison-12-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20industry's%20war%20over%20funding%2C%20talent%2C%20and%20power%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20company%20last%20year%20built%20what%20Musk%20has%20called%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fxai-memphis-supercomputer-gpus-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworld's%20largest%20supercomputer%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Memphis%2C%20Tennessee%2C%20and%20it%20launched%20Grok%20as%20a%20stand-alone%20app%20in%20January.%20xAI%20said%20during%20its%20latest%20funding%20round%20that%20the%20company%20had%20raised%20%246%20billion.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20Musk%20and%20a%20group%20of%20investors%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-elon-musk-97-billion-bid-openai-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esubmitted%20a%20%2497.4%20billion%20bid%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20buy%20the%20nonprofit%20that%20controls%20OpenAI%3B%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%20said%20the%20company%20was%20%26quot%3Bnot%20for%20sale.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20xAI%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c0fa3416-b81e-4bda-8b9c-7f0706991eb5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EInside%20the%20day-to-day%20work%20of%20an%20xAI%20tutor%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EData%20annotators%20play%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20developing%20large%20language%20models.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EBy%20labeling%2C%20categorizing%2C%20and%20contextualizing%20raw%20data%2C%20they%20teach%20chatbots%20like%20Grok%20to%20understand%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tutors%20have%20worked%20on%20various%20projects%20at%20xAI%2C%20including%20improving%20Grok's%20ability%20to%20generate%20images.%20To%20help%20it%20understand%20voice%20commands%2C%20they%20record%20themselves%20in%20noisy%20environments%20and%20analyze%20the%20chatbot's%20transcriptions.%20Three%20workers%20said%20the%20company%20was%20working%20toward%20expanding%20the%20pool%20of%20staffers%20who%20can%20train%20Grok%20in%20different%20languages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20four%20workers%20said%20tutors%20were%20focused%20on%20teaching%20Grok%20to%20understand%2C%20summarize%2C%20and%20provide%20context%20to%20posts%20and%20images%20on%20X.%20(xAI%20rolled%20out%20that%20update%20in%20December.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSometimes%20projects%20take%20months%3B%20sometimes%20it's%20only%20a%20few%20days%20and%20then%20you're%20getting%20a%20message%20from%20a%20team%20lead%20moving%20you%20to%20a%20new%20project%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20worker%20said.%20%26quot%3BSometimes%20it's%20a%20drop-everything%20situation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20xAI%2C%20the%20tutors%20operate%20on%20six-month%20contracts%20as%20full-time%20hourly%20employees%2C%20according%20to%20job%20postings%20and%20conversations%20with%20workers.%20They%20work%20in%20tandem%20with%20engineers%2C%20but%20the%20data%20annotators%20use%20a%20separate%20Slack%2C%20called%20TeachX%2C%20and%20have%20different%20email%20domains%2C%20six%20current%20and%20former%20employees%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20TeachX%2C%20AI%20tutors%20are%20broken%20into%20several%20specialized%20groups%2C%20including%20STEM%2C%20coding%2C%20and%20translation%2C%20as%20well%20as%20a%20much%20larger%20group%20of%20general%20AI%20tutors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20job%20listings%20indicate%20the%20workers%20can%20make%20%2435%20to%20%2465%20an%20hour%20and%20can%20be%20promoted%20to%20team-lead%20roles%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESix%20current%20and%20former%20workers%20said%20that%20while%20most%20tutors%20work%20from%20home%2C%20they're%20supervised%20using%20a%20system%20called%20Starfleet%20Academy%20that%20predicts%20the%20amount%20of%20time%20workers%20should%20spend%20on%20each%20task%2C%20monitors%20their%20screen%20time%2C%20and%20allows%20quality-assurance%20workers%20to%20rate%20their%20work.%20Three%20employees%20said%20workers%20typically%20take%20three%20to%2010%20minutes%20on%20a%20given%20task.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFour%20workers%20said%20that%20the%20tutors%20could%20be%20asked%20to%20justify%20their%20choices%20and%20could%20get%20marked%20down%20if%20a%20quality-assurance%20worker%20disagrees%20with%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMainly%20Starfleet%20is%20a%20way%20to%20make%20sure%20we're%20not%20moving%20too%20fast%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20worker%20said.%20%26quot%3BSometimes%20it%20can%20become%20monotonous%20or%20you%20can%20get%20numb%20to%20flipping%20between%20prompts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2253d21aa3-807e-4cac-991d-c04688ca0635%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EData%20annotators%20are%20crucial%20to%20the%20tech%20industry%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20AI%20tutors%20appear%20to%20make%20up%20most%20of%20xAI's%20workforce.%20A%20review%20of%20LinkedIn%20profiles%20suggests%20the%20company%20has%20about%20100%20noncontract%20employees%2C%20including%20engineers%20and%20technical%20staffers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20most%20AI%20companies%2C%20which%20often%20use%20third-party%20employment%20agencies%2C%20xAI%20hires%20its%20US%20tutors%20directly.%20Otto%20K%C3%A4ssi%2C%20a%20labor%20economist%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Oxford%2C%20said%20this%20model%20allows%20the%20company%20to%20have%20more%20control%20over%20the%20tutors'%20work%20and%20could%20offer%20greater%20data%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ExAI%20is%20far%20from%20the%20only%20company%20leaning%20on%20an%20army%20of%20data%20annotators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%2C%20Musk's%20electric%20vehicle%20manufacturer%2C%20employs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-autopilot-fsd-labeling-facilities-jobs-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehundreds%20of%20in-house%20data%20annotators%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20train%20its%20Full%20Self-Driving%20software.%20Companies%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FOutlier.ai%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOutlier.ai%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Scale%20AI%2C%20SuperAnnotate%2C%20and%20Encord%20also%20provide%20annotators%20for%20Big%20Tech%20companies%20including%20Meta%20and%20Nvidia.%20OpenAI%2C%20which%20Musk%20helped%20found%20before%20resigning%20from%20the%20board%20in%202018%2C%20has%20used%20third-party%20agencies%20that%20can%20hire%20workers%20from%20developing%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20most%20important%20thing%20is%20the%20quantity%20of%20data%2C%26quot%3B%20Stefano%20Ermon%2C%20a%20generative%20AI%20expert%20from%20Stanford%20University%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BThen%20you%20just%20need%20enough%20people%20to%20annotate%20that%20data.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20work%20for%20xAI%20or%20one%20of%20Musk's%20companies%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20the%20reporter%20via%20a%20nonwork%20email%20and%20device%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Agkay%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3Egkay%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20through%20the%20encrypted%20messaging%20platform%20Signal%20at%20248-894-6012.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fxai-elon-musk-hiring-ramp-up-data-annotators-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739351222000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67aa5aac7bb3f854015c65a2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fxai-elon-musk-hiring-ramp-up-data-annotators-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20company%20currently%20e