%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F1SFxM%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22History%20of%20Trump%20tariffs%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221086%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20tariffs%20are%20common%20practice%20across%20countries%20and%20administrations%20to%20regulate%20the%20flow%20of%20goods%20and%20prop%20up%20local%20industries%2C%20Trump%20has%20a%20different%20approach.%20He's%20used%20them%20as%20a%20bargaining%20tool%20in%20both%20his%20first%20and%20second%20terms%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20achieve%20concessions%20from%20other%20countries%20toward%20his%20policy%20goals%2C%20such%20as%20strengthening%20the%20US-Mexico%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20goal%20isn't%20actually%20to%20go%20through%20with%20the%20tariffs%2C%26quot%3B%20Mark%20Jones%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20political%20science%20at%20Rice%20University%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20to%20change%20the%20behavior%20of%20another%20country.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Trump%20has%20already%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efollowed%20through%20on%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etwo%20of%20his%20threats%3A%20sweeping%20tariffs%20on%20all%20Chinese%20imports%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-25-tariffs-steel-aluminum-imports-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eon%20steel%20and%20aluminum%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20any%20country.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20Jones%20said%20that%20Americans%20could%20begin%20seeing%20higher%20prices%20in%20as%20soon%20as%20six%20months%20because%20US%20businesses%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-raising-prices-trump-tariffs-inflation-goods-getting-more-expensive-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewill%20have%20to%20pay%20a%20higher%20price%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20will%20be%20unable%20to%20recreate%20foreign%20goods.%20For%20this%20reason%2C%20Jones%20said%2C%20the%20president's%20goals%20may%20be%20in%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOn%20one%20hand%2C%20he%20wants%20to%20impose%20tariffs%20to%20protect%20American%20industry%20and%20to%20fight%20back%20against%20what%20he%20would%20consider%20to%20be%20unfair%20trade%20practices%2C%26quot%3B%20Jones%20said.%20%26quot%3BOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20he%20wants%20to%20bring%20down%20inflation%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20Those%20two%20policy%20agendas%20are%2C%20in%20some%20ways%2C%20mutually%20exclusive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22136cce56-1f86-4ea2-b3b9-e8b4f313f8e7%5C%22%3ETrump's%20tariff%20playbook%202.0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20first-term%20tariffs%20initially%20affected%20about%20%24380%20billion%20worth%20of%20imports%2C%20which%20is%20about%201.8%25%20of%20America's%20GDP%2C%20Erica%20York%2C%20vice%20president%20of%20federal%20tax%20policy%20at%20the%20Tax%20Foundation%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20comparison%2C%20Trump's%20threatened%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-goods-are-imported-china-mexico-canada-trump-tariff-trade-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etariffs%20on%20Canada%20and%20Mexico%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20imposed%20ones%20on%20China%2C%20would%20impact%20%241.4%20trillion%20of%20imports%2C%20or%204.7%25%20of%20GDP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20before%20we%20consider%20the%20promised%20reciprocal%20tariffs%2C%26quot%3B%20York%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20statements%20from%20Canada%2C%20Mexico%2C%20the%20European%20Union%2C%20and%20others%20that%20they%20would%20retaliate%20in%20the%20event%20of%20tariffs%20against%20them.%20Those%20reciprocal%20tariffs%20would%20hit%20US%20exports%2C%20potentially%20undermining%20the%20very%20industries%20the%20US%20tariffs%20are%20trying%20to%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20face%20of%20those%20higher%20prices%2C%20businesses%20are%20likely%20to%20do%20some%20combination%20of%20passing%20higher%20costs%20along%20to%20final%20consumers%20and%20cutting%20back%20on%20employment%20and%20investment%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJones%20said%20that%20the%20result%20of%20quick%20inflation%20and%20price%20increases%20could%20be%20that%20Americans%20%26quot%3Bfeel%20poor.%20Their%20salaries%20will%20not%20be%20going%20up%2C%20but%20they%20will%20be%20paying%20more%20for%20the%20same%20goods%20that%20they%20normally%20buy%2C%20or%20they%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20buy%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20most%20presidential%20administrations%20%E2%80%94%20regardless%20of%20party%20%E2%80%94%20have%20imposed%20tariffs.%20Beyond%20being%20a%20source%20of%20revenue%20for%20the%20government%2C%20tariffs%20encourage%20foreign%20producers%20to%20keep%20their%20prices%20low%20enough%20to%20compete%20with%20domestically%20made%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20released%20a%20fact%20sheet%20on%20February%2011%20saying%20that%20Trump's%20tariffs%20will%20strengthen%20America's%20manufacturing%20and%20called%20tariffs%20%26quot%3Ban%20effective%20tool%20for%20achieving%20economic%20and%20strategic%20objectives.%26quot%3B%20Trump%20acknowledged%20earlier%20in%20February%20that%20Americans%20would%20feel%20%26quot%3Bsome%20pain%26quot%3B%20as%20a%20result%20of%20his%20tariffs%2C%20but%20added%20that%20the%20pain%20will%20be%20worth%20it%20if%20the%20US%20achieves%20its%20policy%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20tariffs%20on%20China%20from%20Trump's%20first%20term%20and%20kept%20in%20place%20by%20former%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20yielded%20some%20positive%20results%2C%20Ryan%20Hass%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20John%20L.%20Thornton%20China%20Center%20at%20Brookings%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20February%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Fhow-will-the-biden-administrations-china-policy-be-remembered%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblog%20post%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20said%20that%20the%20tariffs%20allowed%20the%20administration%20to%20%26quot%3Bpush%20back%20against%20Chinese%20transgressions%26quot%3B%20and%20strengthen%20American%20competitiveness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEconomists%20and%20policy%20researchers%20BI%20spoke%20with%20agree%20that%20Trump's%20second-term%20tariffs%20are%20a%20step%20up%20from%20his%20previous%20playbook.%20Many%20of%20the%20president's%20first-term%20levies%20were%20smaller%2C%20touched%20fewer%20industries%2C%20or%20were%20never%20enforced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThroughout%202018%20and%202019%2C%20the%20president%20placed%2010%25%20and%2025%25%20tariffs%20on%20hundreds%20of%20billions%20of%20dollars%20worth%20of%20Chinese%20products%20%E2%80%94%20including%20tech%20equipment%20and%20plastics.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20tariff%20strategy%20resulted%20in%20a%20multibillion-dollar%20tax%20increase%20on%20goods%20and%20a%20reduction%20in%20trade%20between%20the%20two%20countries%2C%20per%20The%20Tax%20Foundation.%20China%20responded%20in%202019%20by%20placing%2010%25%20retaliatory%20tariffs%20on%20%2475%20billion%20worth%20of%20US%20imports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20also%20imposed%20and%20repealed%20metals%20tariffs%20on%20Canada%20throughout%20his%20first%20term%2C%20but%20did%20not%20apply%20sweeping%20tariffs.%20His%20last%20attempt%20to%20impose%20a%20tariff%20on%20aluminum%20was%20scrapped%20in%20the%20summer%20of%202020%20to%20avoid%20retaliation%20from%20Canada.%20The%20White%20House%20also%20threatened%20a%205%25%20tariff%20on%20%24346.5%20billion%20of%20imports%20from%20Mexico%20in%202019%20as%20a%20means%20to%20curb%20immigration%2C%20but%20the%20tariffs%20were%20soon%20%26quot%3Bindefinitely%20suspended%26quot%3B%20and%20never%20enforced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20such%20broad%20tariffs%20on%20the%20table%20in%20Trump's%20second%20term%2C%20Jones%20said%20the%20strategy%20may%20not%20be%20worth%20the%20potential%20positives.%20He%20added%20that%20the%20president's%20first-term%20tariffs%20did%20not%20have%20tangible%20benefits%20for%20Americans'%20wallets%2C%20and%20the%20scaled-up%202025%20plan%20could%20come%20at%20an%20undue%20cost%20for%20domestic%20businesses%2C%20consumers%2C%20and%20economic%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20place%20for%20tariffs%20in%20the%20global%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20Jones%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20an%20overreliance%20on%20tariffs%20simply%20to%20protect%20the%20domestic%20industries%20only%20ends%20up%20harming%20the%20economy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-trade-war-what-it-means-for-consumers-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739350862000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ab71f17bb3f854015c786e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-trade-war-what-it-means-for-consumers-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Trump's%20sweeping%20tariff%20strategy%20is%20bigger%20than%20his%20first-term%20in%20office.%20BI%20broke%20down%20what%20the%20trade%20war%20means%20for%20Americans'%20wallets.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22allisonkelly%40businessinsider.com%20(Allie%20Kelly%2CAyelet%20Sheffey)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A25%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-trade-war-what-it-means-for-consumers-2025-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Bridget%20Jones%3A%20Mad%20About%20the%20Boy%E2%80%99%20Review%3A%20Ren%C3%A9e%20Zellweger%20Charms%20in%20What%20Feels%20Like%20a%20Sweetly%20Romantic%20but%20Mild%20Finale%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739350800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F01%2FMCDBRJO_UV003.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1236296617%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22I%20wish%20%26quot%3BMad%20About%20the%20Boy%26quot%3B%20took%20more%20aggressive%20fun%20in%20plugging%20Bridget%2