content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EYour%20columnist%20introduced%20a%20Private%20Member's%20Bill%20during%20this%20session%20of%20Parliament.%20The%20proposed%20legislation%20aims%20at%20removing%20the%20provision%20exempting%20marital%20rape%20in%20India.%20Section%2063%20of%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20(one%20of%20the%20three%20new%20criminal%20laws%20passed%20by%20this%20government)%20continues%20to%20provide%20a%20disturbing%20exception%20for%20marital%20rape%2C%20undermining%20the%20autonomy%20and%20equality%20of%20women.%20This%20archaic%20exception%20sends%20a%20dangerous%20message%E2%80%94that%20a%20woman's%20right%20to%20consent%20is%20irrelevant%20once%20she%20enters%20into%20marriage.%20This%20exception%2C%20rooted%20in%20outdated%20beliefs%20and%20patriarchal%20systems%2C%20is%20not%20just%20an%20affront%20to%20the%20dignity%20of%20women%20but%20also%20a%20direct%20violation%20of%20a%20woman's%20constitutional%20rights%2C%20including%20personal%20liberty%2C%20equality%20and%20privacy.%20The%20new%20Private%20Member's%20Bill%20proposed%20by%20your%20columnist%20seeks%20to%20plug%20this%20loophole%20and%20ensure%20that%20marital%20rape%20is%20not%20excluded%20from%20the%20purview%20of%20criminal%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Origin%20Of%20The%20Exception%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20origins%20of%20the%20marital%20rape%20exception%20can%20be%20traced%20back%20to%2017th-century%20England.%20Sir%20Matthew%20Hale's%20interpretation%20of%20the%20law%20proclaimed%20that%20a%20husband%20could%20not%20be%20guilty%20of%20raping%20his%20wife%20because%2C%20through%20marriage%2C%20the%20wife%20had%20consented%20to%20sexual%20intercourse%20and%20had%20no%20right%20to%20retract%20that%20consent.%20The%20British%20colonial%20legal%20system%20did%20not%20recognise%20the%20equality%20of%20men%20and%20women.%20This%20view%20persisted%20when%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(IPC)%20was%20drafted%20in%20the%2019th%20century.%20Subsequently%2C%20Section%2063%20of%20the%20BNS%20explicitly%20provides%20an%20exception%20to%20the%20definition%20of%20rape%2C%20stating%20that%20sexual%20intercourse%20by%20a%20man%20with%20his%20wife%2C%20who%20is%20over%20the%20age%20of%2018%2C%20cannot%20be%20considered%20rape.%20This%20bizarre%20exception%20has%20remained%2C%20despite%20multiple%20recommendations%20for%20change.%20As%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Joint%20Parliamentary%20Committee%20(JPC)%2C%20which%20(hurriedly)%20examined%20the%20new%20laws%2C%20your%20columnist%20and%20other%20Members%20of%20Parliament%2C%20mainly%20belonging%20to%20Opposition%20parties%2C%20submitted%20dissent%20notes%20objecting%20to%20this%20provision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2042nd%20Report%20of%20the%20Law%20Commission%20(1971)%20suggested%20the%20removal%20of%20this%20exception.%20In%201983%2C%20the%20IPC%20was%20amended%20to%20criminalise%20spousal%20rape.%20This%20exception%20was%20restricted%20to%20cases%20of%20judicial%20separation.%20However%2C%20the%20broader%20exemption%20to%20marital%20rape%20remains%20in%20place.%20International%20bodies%20like%20the%20United%20Nations%20and%20the%20Convention%20on%20the%20Elimination%20of%20All%20Forms%20of%20Discrimination%20Against%20Women%20(CEDAW)%20have%20consistently%20urged%20India%20to%20remove%20this%20exception%2C%20viewing%20it%20as%20a%20violation%20of%20women's%20rights.%20The%20Justice%20Verma%20Committee%2C%20in%20response%20to%20the%20Delhi%20gang%20rape%20case%20of%202012%2C%20also%20recommended%20the%20deletion%20of%20this%20exemption.%20The%20Government%20had%20other%20ideas%E2%80%94choosing%20misogyny%20over%20reform.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Protection%20of%20Women%20from%20Domestic%20Violence%20Act%20(2005)%2C%20while%20recognising%20marital%20rape%20as%20a%20form%20of%20domestic%20violence%2C%20stopped%20short%20of%20criminalising%20it.%20This%20leaves%20married%20women%20vulnerable%20to%20repeated%20assaults%20without%20any%20legal%20recourse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPersonal%20Liberty%20And%20The%20Right%20To%20Reproductive%20Choices%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Right%20to%20Life%20under%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20Constitution%20has%20been%20interpreted%20extensively%20by%20the%20Indian%20judiciary%2C%20and%20in%20its%20attempt%2C%20now%20includes%20the%20right%20to%20live%20with%20dignity%2C%20to%20have%20safe%20living%20conditions%2C%20and%20to%20exercise%20personal%20liberty.%20This%20interpretation%20is%20critical%20when%20discussing%20the%20issue%20of%20marital%20rape.%20The%20sexual%20rights%20of%20a%20woman%20are%20a%20vital%20component%20of%20her%20personal%20liberty.%20The%20exception%20denies%20women%20control%20over%20their%20own%20bodies.%20As%20the%20courts%20have%20recognised%2C%20reproductive%20choices%20include%20the%20right%20to%20abstain%20from%20sex%2C%20use%20contraception%2C%20or%20decide%20not%20to%20have%20children.%20Denying%20women%20this%20discretion%20within%20marriage%20exacerbates%20gender-based%20discrimination%20and%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPrivacy%20And%20The%20Right%20To%20Personal%20Autonomy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20argument%20that%20marital%20rape%20should%20not%20be%20criminalised%20because%20it%20infringes%20on%20marital%20privacy%20is%20based%20on%20a%20deeply%20flawed%20understanding%20of%20both%20privacy%20and%20marriage.%20The%20right%20to%20privacy%2C%20enshrined%20under%20Article%2021%2C%20is%20not%20just%20about%20being%20left%20alone%20but%20also%20about%20the%20liberty%20of%20individuals%20in%20making%20personal%20decisions%2C%20including%20the%20right%20to%20control%20their%20own%20bodies%20and%20sexual%20lives.%20The%20landmark%20Puttaswamy%20judgment%20on%20privacy%20recognised%20that%20decisional%20autonomy%E2%80%94whether%20related%20to%20sexual%20activity%2C%20reproductive%20choices%2C%20or%20personal%20relationships%E2%80%94are%20inviolable.%20Rape%2C%20regardless%20of%20whether%20it%20occurs%20within%20a%20marriage%2C%20is%20a%20violation%20of%20privacy%20and%20bodily%20integrity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EEquality%20Before%20The%20Law%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticle%2014%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%20guarantees%20equality%20before%20the%20law%2C%20yet%20marital%20rape%20laws%20in%20India%20clearly%20discriminate%20against%20women.%20While%20rape%20laws%20recognise%20the%20rights%20of%20women%20in%20general%2C%20the%20exemption%20for%20husbands%20means%20that%20wives%20are%20denied%20equal%20protection%20under%20the%20law.%20The%20exception%20of%20marital%20rape%20is%20not%20only%20a%20legal%20anomaly%3B%20it%20is%20a%20profound%20injustice%20that%20violates%20a%20woman's%20constitutional%20rights%20of%20personal%20liberty%2C%20equality%2C%20and%20dignity.%20The%20Indian%20state%20has%20a%20moral%20and%20legal%20obligation%20to%20protect%20the%20rights%20of%20its%20citizens%2C%20particularly%20women%2C%20and%20to%20ensure%20that%20all%20individuals%2C%20regardless%20of%20marital%20status%2C%20are%20entitled%20to%20equal%20protection%20under%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state's%20failure%20to%20remove%20this%20exception%20only%20perpetuates%20the%20cycle%20of%20violence%20and%20discrimination%20that%20continues%20to%20plague%20women%20in%20marriage%20and%20in%20society.%20It%20is%20time%20for%20the%20Union%20government%2C%20its%20allies%20and%20members%20of%20the%20Opposition%20to%20come%20together%20to%20pass%20a%20law%20that%20reflects%20the%20dignity%2C%20and%20equality%20of%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Derek%20O'Brien%2C%20MP%2C%20leads%20the%20Trinamool%20Congress%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739339160000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2018-10%2Fdcnmvtno_rape-generic_625x300_21_October_18.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2